The paper deals with source coding with side information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves multiterminal settings and cooperation between nodes, which are common in multimedia communication (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also uses examples involving Gaussian and binary sources, which are commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS).
